annotationA: Serpin 38F (Spn38F) is a predicted serine endopeptidase inhibitor. It is expressed in the male accessory glands and transferred to females during mating. Spn38F ectopic expression in females provides anti-microbial protection
annotationB: Ejaculatory bulb-specific protein 1; Major protein component of the posterior mating plug. Accessory gland proteins constitute, or are required for formation of the anterior mating plug. Posterior mating plug forms before sperm transfer and the anterior mating plug is formed after the start of mating
